eturn-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532868\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uvu1665702922300.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uvu1665702922300.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uvu1665702922300.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uvu1665702922300\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Layout of Entities and Fields\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The choices you make in ordering and indexing entity fields can have a negative impact on performance.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d829701e56\">\n                       \n Number of Entities and Fields Painted\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__p_d46283e1_d46284e1_d46285e1\">Keep the number of entities and fields in a form, service, or report as small as possible. For each entity, a hitlist with corresponding data must be administered and each displayed field must be formatted.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d829701e65\">\n                       \n Minimizing Overflow Tables\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__p_d46289e1_d46290e1_d46291e1\">Uniface's maximum record length is 32 KB. If a record containing variable length fields grows to more than 32 KB, Uniface automatically creates and dynamically maintains an overflow table for the entity. Creating overflow tables has a negative impact on performance and should therefore be avoided.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__p_d46292e1_d46293e1_d46294e1\">To avoid creating overflow tables, it can be useful to redefine variable-length fields in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__li_d23045e1_d23046e1_d23047e1\">As a short field of text\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__li_d23048e1_d23049e1_d23050e1\">As a long field in a separate entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__li_d23051e1_d23052e1_d23053e1\">As a short field in an existing entity plus a long field in a separate overflow entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__li_d23054e1_d23055e1_d23056e1\">As more occurrences of fixed length fields in a separate entity\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d829701e95\">\n                       \n Minimizing Compound Keys\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uvu1665702922300__p_d46298e1_d46299e1_d46300e1\">Minimize or avoid the use of compound keys. Compound keys result from cascading key attributes to related entities. Causing key attributes to cascade produces keys of substantial size, expressed in bytes. The number of bytes causes an extra system load in the form of unnecessary I/O. Primary keys are also indexed, so compound keys should be avoided.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532868\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532868\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Layout of Entities and Fields Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Layout of Entities and Fields The choices you make in ordering and indexing entity fields can have a negative impact on performance. Number of Entities and Fields Painted Keep the number of entities and fields in a form, service, or report as small as possible. For each entity, a hitlist with corresponding data must be administered and each displayed field must be formatted. Minimizing Overflow Tables Uniface's maximum record length is 32 KB. If a record containing variable length fields grows to more than 32 KB, Uniface automatically creates and dynamically maintains an overflow table for the entity. Creating overflow tables has a negative impact on performance and should therefore be avoided. To avoid creating overflow tables, it can be useful to redefine variable-length fields in one of the following ways: As a short field of text As a long field in a separate entity As a short field in an existing entity plus a long field in a separate overflow entity As more occurrences of fixed length fields in a separate entity Minimizing Compound Keys Minimize or avoid the use of compound keys. Compound keys result from cascading key attributes to related entities. Causing key attributes to cascade produces keys of substantial size, expressed in bytes. The number of bytes causes an extra system load in the form of unnecessary I/O. Primary keys are also indexed, so compound keys should be avoided. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}